    <text id="B1107T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How answers an inquiry from an L. P. Dangerfield about hiring newly freed blacks.
                    How writes that the government will protect the rights of whites and blacks.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Head Quarters">H<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                            Qrs</abbr> 6th District <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. L. P. Dangerfield<lb/>Rockspring Bath <abbr
                            expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-08-07"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 7<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You are quite at liberty to hire any colored man without the consent of his
                    former master, as he is also at liberty to engage his services without such
                    consent.</p>

                <p>The "citizens" who "resolved that no one should <unclear>hire</unclear>
                    &amp;c" would seem to have been quite willing that white men should lose
                    freedom of action, if only black men could be hindered in the exercise of the
                    freedom they have acquired and cannot lost. Your government however will see
                    that the rights of <hi rend="underline">all</hi> are respected and maintained.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Sir Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>(signed) W. Storer How <abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr>&amp;<abbr
                            expan="Assistant Quartermaster">AQM</abbr><lb/><abbr
                            expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> 6t <abbr expan="District"
                            >Dist.</abbr><abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">True copy of note sent Dangerfield W. Stover How</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
